Source: OIE <http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/a_current.htm>

NEWCASTLE DISEASE IN JAPAN
----------------------------
See also: 2 Jun 2000, 26 May 2000, 21 Jan 2000, 17 Dec 1999
(Date of last previously reported outbreak: May 2000)
Extracts from the monthly reports on the animal health situation in Japan
for Feb and Mar 2001, received from Dr Shigeo Miyajima, Director of Animal
Health Division, Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Tokyo:
Month/ Location/ Number of new outbreaks/ Type of farm
Feb 2001/ Chiba prefecture/ 1 /quail farm
Mar 2001/ Ibaraki prefecture/ 3/ hobby flocks
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
month/ susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
Feb 2001/ 20 213/ 20 213/ 800/ 19 413/ 0
Mar 2001/ 224/ 224/ 108/ 116/ 0
Epidemiology: there was no epidemiological relationship confirmed between
the outbreaks in Ibaraki and the outbreak in Chiba.
Control measures: all susceptible birds kept in the flocks were destroyed.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
